The research suggests that timing is crucial for rotational burning effects, with butterfly abundance generally being higher on areas burned more than one year ago, while leaving unburned patches provides immediate refugia that specialist butterfly species appear to utilize effectively.", "action_ids": ["3883","3879"]}

